{"type":"message","id":"88469cd4","parentId":"3f5da253","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:51.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the pulse results. Let me read the latest log to get the full details.","thinkingSignature":"b62996a39a2cb24aa547821aa4ea8c92d656fe966424f6d7eafb67550d5ece6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dpssiymhja2g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 151316.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3024,"output":73,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379629395}}
{"type":"message","id":"30d59309","parentId":"88469cd4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:51.937Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dpssiymhja2g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 151316\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance the CFI Compression experiment. The key insight is that the hybrid scoring formula needs to be tested:\r\n\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis should distinguish:\r\n- \"Constant format\" tokens: freq≈160, CFI=1.00 → score = 1 × 1 = 1.0 (but capped by min function... wait, freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33, min(1, 1.33) = 1, so score = 1 × 1 = 1.0)\r\n- \"Research trajectory\" tokens: freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score < 1.0\r\n\r\nWait, that's not quite right. Let me recalculate:\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.00 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.00 × min(1, 1.33) = 1.00 × 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- Research trajectory (freq=136, CFI=0.96): score = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96\r\n- Research trajectory (freq=80, CFI=0.7): score = 0.7 × min(1, 80/120) = 0.7 × 0.67 = 0.47\r\n\r\nThe formula as stated doesn't distinguish them well because min(1, freq/120) saturates at 1 for anything above freq=120.\r\n\r\nI think the correct formula should be something like:\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/120) capped at some range\r\n\r\nOr more simply, maybe:\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/160) \r\n\r\n\r\nwhere 160 is the max frequency observed. Looking at the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md, the three-dimensional filter requires CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120). This range excludes both very rare tokens (freq < 3) and common format artifacts (freq ≥ 120). I need to design a PowerShell script that calculates this hybrid score and runs the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid scoring formula in the current spec has a flaw: `min(1, freq/120)` saturates at 1.0 for freq≥120, so constant-format tokens (freq=160) still score near 1.0. Need to correct the formula to use `freq/160` (normalized to max observed frequency).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and prepare the experiment script for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring, with corrected formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/160). Create `experiments/cfi_freq_hybrid.ps1` to run the comparison.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n# Tests: score(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/160)\r\n# Hypothesis: Normalizes by max freq (160) to distinguish constant-format from research trajectory\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$N = 200,\r\n    [double]$TrainSplit = 0.8\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ResultsDir = \"experiments/results\"\r\n$CorpusDir = \"state/corpus\"\r\n$Synthesis = \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\"\r\n\r\n# Ensure directories exist\r\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $ResultsDir | Out-Null\r\n\r\n# Load pulse history for frequency analysis\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \"state/pulses\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n$pulses = $pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw }\r\n\r\n# Build token frequency map\r\n$tokenFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($pulse, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        if ($tokenFreq.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n            $tokenFreq[$token]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $tokenFreq[$token] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token (simplified - in production would use proper continuity calculation)\r\n# CFI = count_in_contiguous_blocks / total_count\r\n# For now, using a proxy: tokens appearing in >80% of pulses have CFI~1.0\r\n\r\n$MAX_FREQ = 160  # Observed max frequency\r\n$tokenData = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $tokenFreq.Keys) {\r\n    $freq = $tokenFreq[$token]\r\n    $cfi = [math]::Min(1.0, ($freq / $pulses.Count) * 1.2)  # Simplified CFI proxy\r\n    $score = $cfi * ($freq / $MAX_FREQ)\r\n    \r\n    $tokenData += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Token = $token\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        CFI = [math]::Round($cfi, 4)\r\n        Score = [math]::Round($score, 4)\r\n        Category = \"\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Categorize tokens\r\nforeach ($t in $tokenData) {\r\n    if ($t.Freq -ge 160 -and $t.CFI -ge 0.95) {\r\n        $t.Category = \"CONSTANT_FORMAT\"\r\n    } elseif ($t.Freq -ge 3 -and\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:13:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379631935}}
