as a flaw: `min(1, freq/120)` saturates at 1.0 for freq≥120, so constant-format tokens (freq=160) still score near 1.0. Need to correct the formula to use `freq/160` (normalized to max observed frequency).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and prepare the experiment script for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring, with corrected formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/160). Create `experiments/cfi_freq_hybrid.ps1` to run the comparison.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n# Tests: score(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/160)\r\n# Hypothesis: Normalizes by max freq (160) to distinguish constant-format from research trajectory\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$N = 200,\r\n    [double]$TrainSplit = 0.8\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ResultsDir = \"experiments/results\"\r\n$CorpusDir = \"state/corpus\"\r\n$Synthesis = \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\"\r\n\r\n# Ensure directories exist\r\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $ResultsDir | Out-Null\r\n\r\n# Load pulse history for frequency analysis\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \"state/pulses\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n$pulses = $pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw }\r\n\r\n# Build token frequency map\r\n$tokenFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($pulse, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        if ($tokenFreq.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n            $tokenFreq[$token]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $tokenFreq[$token] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token (simplified - in production would use proper continuity calculation)\r\n# CFI = count_in_contiguous_blocks / total_count\r\n# For now, using a proxy: tokens appearing in >80% of pulses have CFI~1.0\r\n\r\n$MAX_FREQ = 160  # Observed max frequency\r\n$tokenData = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $tokenFreq.Keys) {\r\n    $freq = $tokenFreq[$toke